rComments: Quan is a young homie around the block who's super caring for his students but makes the course a pain in the ass in terms of total evaluations over the semester.

Honestly the best prof I've ever had, I hope to have more classes with him in the future. He genuinely cares about students' success and always did his best to make lectures as engaging as possible. Super accessible outside of class time and the course is an easy A as long as you show up to class.

One of the best professors I have ever had! He explains everything very clearly in class and genuinely cares about all his students. He is very accessible outside of class and willing to meet with you about anything you want to talk about. Exams are very fair, questions are mostly from lectures and rarely from the textbook.

Jeffry was not only a professor but a friend. He got to know most student's names and gave constructive feedback on our work. His tests and assignments were fair and he is generous with bonus points and study tips. His class resembles PSY1102 which made the workload more manageable. I am hoping I can take more classes with him in the future.
Ugh, just ugh. Grading on assignments not clear, exams sooooo long and he is just not very helpful. Avoid.

He is a new prof and it really felt like he was trying to prove himself. While he knows his stuff and is competent, his exams are so wordy and long that it was frustrating just getting through all the questions. Grades very strictly on writing assignments. Needs to ease up, class had potential but in the end I wish I had picked another elective.
